'''Fevziye Rahgozar Barlas''' (born 1955 [[Balkh]]) is an Afghan [[poet]], and [[short story writer]].

==Life==
She is the daughter of [[Shafee Rahgozar]].
She graduated high school in [[Kabul]], and married Rai Barlas.
She graduated from [[Istanbul University]] in 1977.
She worked for the Minister for Information and Culture.
In 1979, she went into exile.
She was a Senior Editor and News Anchor, [[Radio Free Europe]] / Radio Liberty.<ref>http://www.indiana.edu/~afghan/uncertain_times.htm</ref> 
She graduated from [[University of Washington]] with an MA in 1996.
<ref>{{cite book| url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Y-TMhtk5AUYC&pg=PA29&dq=Fevziye+Rahgozar+Barlas&hl=en&ei=g7kITuqJLtL1gAfP1sXqDQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Fevziye%20Rahgozar%20Barlas&f=false| title=Who's who in contemporary women's writing| editor= Jane Eldridge Miller| publisher= Psychology Press| year= 2001| isbn= 9780415159807 }}</ref>

==Works==
*''Dayer-e Shegeftiha (Wonderland)'', 1999
*''The Heavens are my Father'', 2001

*''Wondering Eyes''

